-- Russian Equity Movers: Mechel, Sberbank, VTB Group Are Active
-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 2012-04-03T15:36:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/russian-equity-movers-mechel-sberbank-vtb-group-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  jumped 1.8
percent to 1,550.05 by the close in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index rallied 2.4 percent to 1,681.8.  The following are among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis:  OAO Mechel (MTLR)  (MTLR RX), Russia’s largest producer of coal for
steelmakers, rose a third day after a watchdog declined to pull
licenses for the company’s Southern Kuzbass unit, according to
RIA Novosti.  Mechel (MTLR)  advanced 3.9 percent at 279.3 rubles.  OAO Sberbank (SBER)  (SBER RX), Russia’s largest bank, climbed for
a third day as the ruble strengthened against the dollar. The
stock advanced 2.9 percent to 97.92 rubles.  VTB Group (VTBR)  (VTBR RX),  Russia ’s second-largest bank, also
increased a third day, adding 2 percent to 6.969 kopeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
